The paper deals with a robotic manipulation task, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves the use of neural networks to process RGB-D images, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also mentions the evaluation of the approach based on success rate and number of required push actions, indicating the use of statistical analysis and optimization, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
